-- Cardinals Beat Giants 6-4 in Opening Game of MLB Playoff Series
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2012-10-15T03:39:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-15/cardinals-beat-giants-6-4-in-opening-game-of-mlb-playoff-series.html
David Freese and  Carlos Beltran  hit
two-run home runs and the  St. Louis  Cardinals defeated the host
San Francisco Giants 6-4 in the opening game of the National
League Championship Series.  Game 2 of the best-of-seven Major League Baseball playoff
series is set for tomorrow night in San Francisco.  In the American League, the Detroit Tigers defeated the New
York Yankees 3-0 to take a two-games-to-none lead in their
championship series. Both games have been in New York.  The Cardinals jumped out to a 6-0 lead and then held on as
the Giants scored four unanswered runs. St. Louis used seven
pitchers in the game.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  